nit: Change title to something like

'meta-hpe: enable host power-on and sensors in packagegroups'

- "Update" is redundant because all commits are an "update".
- When your diff touches a meta-layer, specify that meta-layer first so top-level reviewers can avoid it easier and others can quickly filter out commits that aren't relevant to them.
- prefer lower case in commit messages.
I really appreciate the writeup, thanks!
Please avoid tabs.  We use spaces almost everywhere except for kernel (or a few repositories which follow upstream kernel coding conventions).
Done
This had a +2 before things were held up by a merge conflict that has now been resolved.
spaces instead of tabs please.
Ah, I didn't think about spacing while accepting the merge conflict changes. Fix incoming.

It's not recommended that you add differences between Gerrit revisions in your commit message.  The commit message gets applied to the repository as-is, so this information is not useful at that point (and has the potential to confuse someone in the future).

I've gone ahead and updated any reviews I've got that include a statement like that.

Thanks for the advice!
